<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="138" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,958,1919]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,381,1318,1343]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Measurements.</emphasis>
Head length (1.4–1.6); head width (2.3–2.5); pronotum length (2.5–2.6); pronotum width (6.5–7.2); scutellum length (5.2–5.6); scutellum width (4.1–4.6); length of antennal segments (I: 1.1–1.5; II: 1–1.5; III: 2.1–2.5; IV: 2.6–2.8; V: 2.3–2.9); total length (11.3–13); abdominal width (7.3–7.8).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,958,1919]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1426,1451]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Diagnose.</emphasis>
Head not punctured. Pronotum not rugose. Arms of the anterior bifurcation of the metasternal process (
<figureCitation box="[253,350,1462,1487]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[232,1369,202,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[208,1399,177,1927]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. A – E. Edessa viridula sp. n.: A – C, pygophore in dorsal, ventral and posterior view, respectively; D, genital plates; E, metasternal process. dr—dorsal rim; vr—ventral rim; proc—proctiger; pa – parameres; gc 8 — gonocoxites 8; gc 9 — gonocoxites 9; l – ventral lobes of the paramere; lat 8 — laterotergites 8; lat 9 — laterotergites 9; x- tenth segment. Scale 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/545753/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Fig. 1 E</figureCitation>
) long and rounded apically, receiving fourth rostral segment almost entirely. Peritreme almost reaching half of the distance between ostiole of the scent gland and lateral margin of the body (
<figureCitation box="[1314,1424,1498,1523]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1959,1981]" captionTargetBox="[212,1372,254,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[200,1387,193,1938]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. A – E. Peritreme: A, Edessa viridula sp. n.; B, Edessa exigusternata sp. n.; C, Edessa angusticlada sp. n.; D, Edessa rugulata sp. n.; E, Edessa eucnema sp. n.. Scale 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/545760/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Fig. 8 A</figureCitation>
). Evaporatorium with a long and raised crest in mesopleuron delimited by sulci; contiguous margin of meso and metapleuron also raised; metapleuron with two distinct raised crests one short medial and the other long distal. Spiracles concolorous with abdominal sternites; trichobothria placed in light yellow callous. Antennae and legs spotless.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,958,1919]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1678,1703]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[274,406,1678,1703]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[232,1369,202,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[208,1399,177,1927]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. A – E. Edessa viridula sp. n.: A – C, pygophore in dorsal, ventral and posterior view, respectively; D, genital plates; E, metasternal process. dr—dorsal rim; vr—ventral rim; proc—proctiger; pa – parameres; gc 8 — gonocoxites 8; gc 9 — gonocoxites 9; l – ventral lobes of the paramere; lat 8 — laterotergites 8; lat 9 — laterotergites 9; x- tenth segment. Scale 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/545753/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Figs 1 A–C</figureCitation>
). Superior process of the genital cup formed by a line of tiny brown tubercles. Basal part of the paramere wider than its distal portion, with two distinct globose lobes (
<figureCitation box="[983,1077,1714,1739]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[232,1369,202,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[208,1399,177,1927]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. A – E. Edessa viridula sp. n.: A – C, pygophore in dorsal, ventral and posterior view, respectively; D, genital plates; E, metasternal process. dr—dorsal rim; vr—ventral rim; proc—proctiger; pa – parameres; gc 8 — gonocoxites 8; gc 9 — gonocoxites 9; l – ventral lobes of the paramere; lat 8 — laterotergites 8; lat 9 — laterotergites 9; x- tenth segment. Scale 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/545753/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Fig. 1 C</figureCitation>
); distal lobe curved posteriorly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,958,1919]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1750,1775]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Female</emphasis>
(
